# Contracts

Semantic backbone for federated but harmonized enterprise entities.

Establishes the top-level contracts/ directory as the semantic backbone of the repository.

This folder will contain versioned identity contracts, attribute authority maps, matching rules, and enrichment boundaries that define canonical entities in a federated but semantically harmonized architecture.

Contracts represent structural truth definitions (e.g., Customer, Account, Transaction) and sit upstream of PM artifacts and applied AI projects. They formalize:

Canonical entity definitions

Attribute-level designated and effective systems of record

Identity key strategy and matching rules

Enrichment boundaries and projection constraints

Structural quality gates tied to identity maturity

These contracts enable consistent identity coherence, structured remediation tracking, and AI eligibility gating across federated systems without introducing centralized data monoliths.

This directory establishes the foundational semantic layer for the enterprise AI operating model.
